Stepping into the year detaching from the things that don’t allow me to excel.. this year, I make music to not gain position or approval, but to flow as authentic as possible. Im not chasing approval nor those who aren’t interested in what I have to offer. Freedom is everything! A huge part of that detachment is myself. Acknowledging your flaws and bad habits is the first step to clearing up the clutter. I have a lot.. feeling great and motivated! Let’s get it #TeamRonny 
Cheers to a new year, to new music, new stages, new beginnings, chapters and to all the things we are already grateful for, including you. 🥂

Lagrimas @lavozus #TBT on my bday 1/19/2019🎂4 years already! Hace 4 años, en el día de mi cumpleaños esta presentación fue vista por todo el mundo cambiándome la vida. Estaba tan nervioso pero Muy emocionado de estar en esa tarima. El video Género más de 6.5 MILLIONES de views en YT (antes de que lo quitaran de la página oficial del programa- al menos si tengo el screenshot lol) y fue uno de los regalos más bonitos de mi vida. 
Hoy en mis conciertos aun es la canción más pedida.. Nunca lo hubiese imaginado. Aun Le doy gracias a Dios, La Voz/Telemundo y al público que me sigue apoyando desde el primer día!  Dios les bendiga. Agradecido también con @wisin por creer en mi. #TeamWisin Tambien a @luisfonsi 🙏🏾 thank you bro! … y a @carlosvives y @laguzmanmx 
Este video es muy especial para mi porque me motiva Siempre seguir adelante cuando mas necesito motivación.
🎂🎤🎂🎤🎂🎤🎂🎤🎂
4 years ago, on my bday, this performance aired worldwide!  I was so nervous but so excited to be on that stage! Generating over 6.5 Million views  on YT(before it was taken down From the show’s YT page), it was one of the most treasured gifts I have ever received thanks to God, La Voz/Telemundo @telemundo @telemundorealities and the audience.
Lagrimas is still the most acclaimed song in my concerts! Lol. I would’ve never imagined that!

@lamarlenemaseda with @fusion4media ,
@gdiliz

I’d like to honorably mention a great friend and mentor who never stops encouraging me @henrysantos THANK YOU HENRY! 😁✌️

Step 1. Let Go
Sometimes you have to be put in uncomfortable situations in order to move on to the next chapter. We won’t know how the story unfolds until we turn the page…
Step 2. Clarity
You will never get what you want if you are unsure of what it is you really want. Be clear when you manifest/pray … be honest with yourself and transparent with your word.
Step 3. Believe 
Faith is the fuel of action.
Know that God will always have your back when you believe, act with honesty and with a pure heart.

Everything has a solution, you just have to make time to figure out the puzzle. What is it you must learn from this experience to move forward? #time #patience #work #motivation #process #life #keepgoing #yougotthis

What holds us back from attracting our best lives is unfocused intention. You may have the right desires to achieve your goals and may even do the right things, but, when we allow fear, doubt or insecurities to play any part of managing our dreams, we put a wall in front of us and continue to manifest the things we don’t want. I write from experience.. I am guilty of falling into this many times which is why I never speak out my plans until things happen for me. Japan was one of them. I quietly worked hard at constructing a great tour and …. We did it! I am so grateful to my team at MME for making it all come together. 
Cheers to you and the things you are working on! Never give up! Life offers us so much to grab from and help us in our journey. God bless you and may we accomplish the things we desire! 🇯🇵 
#Nagoya #Japan #Beach #Manifest #Pray #Positive

#canthelpfallinginlove is what describes my look as my wife accidentally passes through while I try to film myself singing this, causing me to interpret this classic differently. Love became the captain of my ship and began navigating differently..
Besides technique, Great singing requires two main ingredients: intention and truth. People will always feel truth and will always gravitate towards it because truth is always what we seek. 
We are living in times in which emotions are becoming fabricated and for some, make believe or just a state of mind. Music makes me feel alive and pure, genuine love is what moves me. This moment reminded me of that. Thanks babe for inspiring me everyday… @deborahparata #tiamo #love #lovesongs

Thank you Chicago! Here’s a little sound check from yesterdays 4th of July event in Elgin Illinois… 
I admit, I was so scared about singing because I recently had oral surgery and am still healing. I woke up with swollen cheeks and sore gums with only one hour of sleep. I also forgot my meds in NY!! 😳 Thank God 🙏🏽 for coffee, the ice in the hotel lobby, adrenaline and the love of the crowd. ❤️ Technique will also help you if you are ever in trouble physically, which is why I always recommend singers to train their instrument…
As soon I went on stage, I forgot about the discomfort and enjoyed every second of it! Music really is healing and so is the love of an amazing audience! Had a blast! Until next time Chicago! Gracias.. 
#amazinggrace #singer #music #concert #livemusic #lavoz #thevoice

I post this video not only to remember 9/11 but also because these images hit hard! 😔 I do this because I want to make awareness of what happened, really happened that day for those who go to the 9/11 memorial to take happy selfies for their social media or vendors who capitalize on their 9/11 merch. 
it was my 1st day of school, sophomore year in high school and I was in math class. When everything got interrupted by the news of a bomb in one of the towers. Moments after, my classmates and I went to the computer lab to watch the news to see all of the events unfold. More information came in as the news then clarified it was a plane. Immediately after a second plane hit the second tower. It was the 1st time I ever heard the word terrorism. Then we witnessed the twin towers fall. I remember looking out the window and seeing the sky half black and half blue for weeks, as if a piece of the earths ceiling had fallen down. 
The victims of 911 didn’t chose to die which is why it bothers me to see merchandise or insensitive actions taken when it comes to remembering this day. It will always be a real tragedy for me and many of us who lived these moments in NYC, especially for the families of the victims of 9/11.
One thing it did was unite NYC a bit more as perfect strangers showed love and support to one another in the streets through prayers, hymns and candlelight vigils.
I still remember how impressive they were. Was even fortunate enough to go all the way up 4 times as a kid. #neverforget #911 #nyc
